H0.text: In the northern hemisphere, what season begins in one calendar year and ends in the next. Autumn

H1.text: In the northern hemisphere, what season begins in one calendar year and ends in the next. Spring

H2.text: In the northern hemisphere, what season begins in one calendar year and ends in the next. Indian Summer

H3.text: In the northern hemisphere, what season begins in one calendar year and ends in the next. Winter

A4.text: In the Northern Hemisphere, winter is defined as starting on 1 December and ending on 1 March.

A5.text: In the Northern Hemisphere, spring is defined as starting on 1 March and ending on 1 June.

A9.text: In the Northern Hemisphere, the March equinox marks the beginning of spring.

A11.text: In the Northern Hemisphere, autumn is defined as starting on 1 September and ending on 1 December.
